    <sys:String x:Key="LocAdv_ConcurrentConversionsSingle">Single conversion: run one operation at a time. This is the safest option for HDD storage and laptops.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LocAdv_ConcurrentConversionsBalanced">Dual conversion: run two operations at the same time. Good balance for mid-range devices.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LocAdv_ConcurrentConversionsHeavy">Heavy conversion: run three operations at the same time. Powerful option, but it may affect system responsiveness when the disk or CPU is under load.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LocAdv_ConcurrentConversionsMaximum">Maximum load: run four operations at the same time. Intended for high-end devices; heat may rise and system responsiveness may drop.</sys:String>

